<!-- Intro -->
<div class="flex page-canvas">
	<div class="flex-item-1col">
		<p class="lead">Red Sweater Project offers high-quality middle and high school education for kids in rural East Africa. Wonder Woman has her cape and Zorro has his mask. In Tanzania, a school uniform is transformational. Putting on a red sweater means having the opportunity to learn and to better an entire community.</p>
		<div class="btns-wrapper mt-4">
      <%= link_to 'Check out the school', schools_path, :class=> "btn btn-solid"%>
		</div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<!-- IT STARTS WITH A SWEATER -->
<div class="flex page-canvas">
  <div class="flex-item-1col">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6" style="">
        <h2>IT STARTS WITH A SWEATER</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          At the Mungere School, students learn creative problem solving and to use their education to invest in themselves, their families, their villages and the world. It's a ripple effect. And it starts with a red sweater.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3"><strong>COMMON THREADS</strong></p>
        <p class="">
          Red and blue colors, traditionally worn by the indigenous Masaai tribe, inspired our school uniform of red sweaters with blue skirts or pants. This design represents our commitment to enhance&mdash;not replace&mdash;tribal heritage.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6 startssweater">
        <img alt="Student in a read sweater" src="/images/home-starts-sweater.jpg" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

